citation.name: Assessing Neuroprotective Agents for Aβ-Induced Neurotoxicity.

links.evidence: Aβ has been shown to interact with various receptors to induce synaptic and neuronal dysfunction and death. Targets notably include cellular prion protein (PrPc) [59,60] coupled to the metabotropic glutamate receptor 5 (mGluR5) [59,61], amylin receptors [62–64], NMDA-type glutamate receptors (and perhaps AMPA glutamate receptors) [65,66], and nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChRs) [67–69].
